libpoc (1.1.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * srv: per-group replay ring (last 2 s) drained to a client on its
    first UDP punch when the group is mid-broadcast. Late joiners
    (e.g. iOS waking via APNs while RF is keyed) no longer miss the
    head of the transmission.
  * srv: log NAT remap / source-port change on incoming UDP — gives
    a clear signal when iOS reconnects from a fresh NAT pinhole.

 -- Brian West <brian@kerchunk.net>  Fri, 09 May 2026 14:00:00 +0000

libpoc (1.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * push: defer APNs token send until POC_STATE_ONLINE.
    Pre-auth 0x90 frames raced into the login state machine and
    deadlocked the I/O thread because poc_resend_push_token_if_set
    relocked the sig_mutex its caller already held; both behaviors
    are fixed. Public API unchanged.

 -- Brian West <brian@kerchunk.net>  Thu, 08 May 2026 16:00:00 +0000

libpoc (1.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Opus-only audio. Speex NB/WB/UWB, G.711 PCMU/PCMA removed.
  * Codec is hardcoded Opus super-wideband: 24 kHz, 20 ms frames,
    32 kbps VBR, inband FEC at 10 % loss target, complexity 10.
  * Custom packet-level FEC (poc_fec.c) replaced by Opus inband FEC.
  * poc_config_t loses `codec`, `enable_fec`, `fec_group_size`.
  * poc_server_config_t loses any codec field (single codec).
  * libspeex build dependency removed; libopus now required.
  * ABI break — bump SONAME via -version-info on next release tag.

 -- Brian West <brian@kerchunk.net>  Thu, 07 May 2026 16:00:00 +0000

